(
<figureCitation box="[527,662,1322,1349]" captionStart="FIGURES 49–57" captionStartId="38.[151,264,1907,1931]" captionTargetBox="[170,1418,181,1882]" captionTargetId="figure-32@38.[170,1418,181,1883]" captionTargetPageId="38" captionText="FIGURES 49–57. Habitus images of Cyrtocapsus spp. 49–51, C. rostratus. 49, male dorsal aspect. 50, female lectotype, dorsal aspect. 51, female lectotype, lateral aspect. 52–54, C. schaffneri. 52, male, dorsal aspect. 53, female, dorsal aspect. 54, C. female, lateral aspect. 55, C. spatulatus, holotype male, dorsal aspect. 56, 57. C. suturalis. 56, male, dorsal aspect. 57, male, lateral aspect." pageId="43" pageNumber="44">Figs. 56, 57</figureCitation>
): Length to apex of membrane 
<quantity box="[1005,1106,1323,1349]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.8" pageId="43" pageNumber="44" unit="mm" value="3.8">3.80 mm</quantity>
, length to base of cuneus 
<quantity metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.48" pageId="43" pageNumber="44" unit="mm" value="2.48">2.48 mm</quantity>
, widest width across hemelytra 
<quantity box="[559,662,1358,1385]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.54" pageId="43" pageNumber="44" unit="mm" value="1.54">1.54 mm</quantity>
. 
<emphasis box="[674,735,1359,1385]" italics="true" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">Head</emphasis>
: Width 
<quantity box="[826,928,1359,1385]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.6" pageId="43" pageNumber="44" unit="mm" value="0.86">0.86 mm</quantity>
, interocular width 
<quantity box="[1141,1245,1358,1385]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.5" pageId="43" pageNumber="44" unit="mm" value="0.45">0.45 mm</quantity>
. 
<emphasis box="[1256,1342,1359,1385]" italics="true" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">Labium</emphasis>
: Length 
<quantity box="[151,255,1395,1421]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.9" pageId="43" pageNumber="44" unit="mm" value="0.99">0.99 mm</quantity>
. 
<emphasis box="[266,359,1395,1421]" italics="true" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">Antenna</emphasis>
: Segment I length 
<quantity box="[577,681,1394,1421]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.5" pageId="43" pageNumber="44" unit="mm" value="0.45">0.45 mm</quantity>
; II, 
<quantity box="[727,831,1395,1421]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.8999999999999995" pageId="43" pageNumber="44" unit="mm" value="0.69">0.69 mm</quantity>
; III, 
<quantity box="[886,990,1394,1421]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.1" pageId="43" pageNumber="44" unit="mm" value="0.51">0.51 mm</quantity>
; IV, missing. 
<emphasis box="[1146,1257,1395,1420]" italics="true" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">Pronotum</emphasis>
: Median length 
<quantity box="[151,253,1431,1457]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.8" pageId="43" pageNumber="44" unit="mm" value="0.88">0.88 mm</quantity>
, basal width 
<quantity box="[400,503,1431,1457]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.26" pageId="43" pageNumber="44" unit="mm" value="1.26">1.26 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="43.[151,1437,1106,2033]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">
<emphasis box="[199,322,1467,1493]" italics="true" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">Coloration</emphasis>
: Head brownish orange dorsally, sides of clypeus fuscous, undersurface pale yellowish white; eyes dark reddish brown. Labium pale yellowish white. Antenna uniformly pale yellowish white. Pronotum brown, more brownish orange through middle of disc, collar and calli black. Scutellum brownish orange, margined in black. Hemelytron brownish orange, with costal vein, claval suture, and narrow inner margin of clavus fuscous; cuneus slightly darker brown along inner margin; membrane clear, veins brown, inside of areole smoky brown. Undersurface of thorax, including ostiolar auricle black; abdomen dark brown, with margins of segments fuscous. Legs uniformly pale yellowish white.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="43.[151,1437,1106,2033]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">
<emphasis box="[199,439,1719,1745]" italics="true" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">Texture and vestiture</emphasis>
: Head weakly shiny, rugose, and transversely striate on frons, with silvery sericeous, especially along inner margins of eyes, median line, and transversely across striations. Pronotum weakly shiny, disc evenly punctate, punctures finer on calli and collar, with silvery sericeous setae (setae on calli and collar rubbed and contaminated with a white residue). Hemelytron dull, impunctate, with scattered patches of short, slender, silvery, sericeous setae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="43.[151,1437,1106,2033]" box="[199,733,1899,1925]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">
<emphasis box="[199,364,1899,1925]" italics="true" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">Male gentialia</emphasis>
: Unique specimen not dissected.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="43.[151,1437,1106,2033]" box="[199,416,1935,1961]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">
<emphasis box="[199,283,1935,1961]" italics="true" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">Female</emphasis>
: Unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="43" pageNumber="44" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="43.[151,1437,1106,2033]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1971,1997]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific epithet “suturalis” is given to denote the distinctive fuscous claval suture of this species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
